52 bool ThermoDB::load(const SpeciesListDescriptor& descriptor)
53 {
54  // It is possible that this isn't the first call to load so just make sure
55  // species and elements are cleared
56  m_species.clear();
57  m_elements.clear();
58 
59  // Load all possible species from the concrete database type
60  std::list<Species> species_list;
61  loadAvailableSpecies(species_list);
62 
63  // Check for duplicate species in the database
64  std::list<Species>::iterator iter1 = species_list.begin();
65  std::list<Species>::iterator iter2;
66 
67  while (iter1 != species_list.end()) {
68  (iter2 = iter1)++;
69  while (iter2 != species_list.end()) {
70  if (iter1->name() == iter2->name()) {
71  std::cout << "Warning, species \"" << iter1->name()
72  << "\" is defined more than once in the thermodynamic"
73  << " database. I will ignore recurrences..."
74  << std::endl;
75  iter2 = species_list.erase(iter2);
76  while (iter2 != species_list.end()) {
77  if (iter1->name() == iter2->name())
78  iter2 = species_list.erase(iter2);
79  else
80  iter2++;
81  }
82  } else
83  iter2++;
84  }
85  iter1++;
86  }
87 
88  // Use the species list descriptor to remove unwanted species
89  iter1 = species_list.begin();
90  while (iter1 != species_list.end()) {
91  if (descriptor.matches(*iter1))
92  iter1++;
93  else
94  iter1 = species_list.erase(iter1);
95  }
96 
97  // Now we have all of the species that we want but possibly in the wrong
98  // order so use the descriptor to tell us the correct order
99  std::vector<std::string> missing;
100  descriptor.order(species_list, m_species, missing);
101 
102  if (missing.size() > 0) {
103  std::cout << "Missing the following species!" << std::endl;
104  for (int i = 0; i < missing.size(); ++i)
105  std::cout << " " << missing[i] << std::endl;
106  return false;
107  }
108 
109  // Finally fill our elements vector with only the elements that are required
110  // for the species list
111  std::set<std::string> element_names;
112  for (int i = 0; i < m_species.size(); ++i) {
113  Species::StoichList::const_iterator iter =
114  m_species[i].stoichiometry().begin();
115  for ( ; iter != m_species[i].stoichiometry().end(); ++iter)
116  element_names.insert(iter->first);
117  }
118 
119  for (int i = 0; i < Element::database().size(); ++i)
120  if (element_names.count(Element::database()[i].name()) > 0)
121  m_elements.push_back(Element::database()[i]);
122 
123  // Tell the concrete class to load the necessary thermodynamic data based on
124  // the final species list
125  loadThermodynamicData();
126  return true;
127 }

131 // Used in ThermoDB::cv
132 struct MinusOne {
133  void operator () (double& x) const { x -= 1.0; }
134 } MinusOne;
135 
136 void ThermoDB::cv(
137  double Th, double Te, double Tr, double Tv, double Tel,
138  double* const cv = NULL, double* const cvt = NULL, double* const cvr = NULL,
139  double* const cvv = NULL, double* const cvel = NULL)
140 {
141  // Compute Cp/Ru
142  cp(Th, Te, Tr, Tv, Tel, cv, cvt, cvr, cvv, cvel);
143 
144  const size_t ns = m_species.size();
145 
146  // Cv/Ru = Cp/Ru - 1
147  if (cv != NULL) std::for_each( cv+0, cv+ns, MinusOne);
148  if (cvt != NULL) std::for_each( cvt+0, cvt+ns, MinusOne);
149  if (cvr != NULL) std::for_each( cvr+0, cvr+ns, MinusOne);
150  if (cvv != NULL) std::for_each( cvv+0, cvv+ns, MinusOne);
151  if (cvel != NULL) std::for_each(cvel+0, cvel+ns, MinusOne);
152 }

184 void ThermoDB::cpint(double T, double* const p_cp) {
185  cp(T, T, T, T, T, p_cp);
186  Map<ArrayXd>(p_cp, m_species.size()) -= 2.5;
187 }
